The paper deals with interactive image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper focuses on designing an efficient and user-friendly interaction mechanism for annotation on small touchscreen devices, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions enforcing sparsity and diversity criteria on the selection of query seeds, which could be related to graph theory and combinatorics (cs.GR). The evaluation of the algorithm involves measuring segmentation accuracy and response time, which could be considered as multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks, respectively.
